# Kernel / Arch Layering

## Dependency Direction

```
kernel/ → arch/ (via ulmk_arch.h API only)
arch/   → board/ (via board primitives, e.g. ulmk_printk_char_out)
board/  → nothing above
```

**arch/ must NEVER depend on kernel/ internals** (no `#include <kernel/include/...>`).
**kernel/ must NEVER contain arch-specific code** (no `mfcr`, `mtcr`, `__asm__` with CSFRs, CSA layout, TriCore register names).

## Contracts

| Symbol prefix | Lives in | Called by |
|---|---|---|
| `ulmk_arch_*` | `arch/tricore/` | `kernel/` only |
| `ulmk_kernel_*` | `kernel/` | `arch/tricore/` only (callbacks) |
| `ulmk_printk_char_out` | board (weak symbol) | arch + kernel |

## Fault handler pattern

```c
/* kernel/kernel_main.c — NO arch code */
void ulmk_kernel_trap_fault(uint8_t trap_class, uint8_t tin)
{
    ulmk_printk("TRAP class=%u tin=%u\n", trap_class, tin);
    ulmk_arch_trap_dump(trap_class, tin); /* arch does the hw-specific dump */
    for (;;);
}

/* arch/tricore/arch.c — all PCXI/CSA/CSFR logic lives here */
void ulmk_arch_trap_dump(uint8_t trap_class, uint8_t tin) { ... }
```

## Adding a new arch operation

1. Declare `ulmk_arch_foo()` in `arch/tricore/include/ulmk_arch.h`
2. Implement in `arch/tricore/arch.c` (or a sub-file `arch/tricore/foo.c`)
3. Call from `kernel/` through the declared prototype
4. Never inline the implementation in a kernel source file

## Style:

Kernel MUST not have comments that reference a particular architecture, just general architecture layer comments.